REASONING: The official CPF Board page states: "You can apply to withdraw your CPF savings from age 55 onwards" and explicitly notes "The minimum withdrawal age for CPF savings is 55 years old, not 50."

The Ministry of Manpower (MOM) official page says: "The CPF withdrawal age is 55 years old. Members can withdraw their CPF savings above the Full Retirement Sum from age 55," and warns information claiming withdrawal at 50 is incorrect.

Ask.gov.sg (official government Q&A) answers: "The minimum age for CPF withdrawal is 55 years old. You cannot withdraw your CPF at 50," and explains exceptions (medical, leaving Singapore permanently) but no general withdrawal at 50.
